From http://forums.atlassian.com/thread.jspa?messageID=257250330#257250330, 
{quote}
Disabling a build queue is not persistent between restarts. This is annoying as we have a number of build queues that all tried to run at once as soon as bamboo is restarted. I wanted to turn them on one at a time to make sure they worked. I ended up disabling each build individually which did work.
{quote}

To replicate this scenario;
1) Create build queue
2) Disable build queue
3) Up on restart, the build queue's are enabled.

Thank you Mark(mg) for reporting this issue.

Peter from BAM-957
{quote}
As we are already using JIRA with mssql server, it makes sense for us to also use mssql server for bamboo too. Are there any plans to support mssql databases and if so when would the support be likely to be implemented.
{quote}

From, http://forums.atlassian.com/thread.jspa?messageID=257250220#257250220
{quote}
It's very limiting that the Build Plan Keys are limited to uppercase
alphanumerics. I would very much like to be able to punch in lower case
and separators. 
{quote}

It'd be good if Bamboo automatically kills a build if it detects that input is required... This solves problems with being stuck when something like this happens

{noformat}
The authenticity of host 'repository.atlassian.com' can't be established.
RSA key fingerprint is 11:54:1f:4a:d3:90:9c:e2:10:22:79:50:83:31:a7:c0.
{noformat}

On large Bamboo instances with large tests (results) the performance suffers, while Bamboo tries to parse the past test results and drill down to retrieve data from the build-results.xml file

Originally a support issue [BAM-166|https://support.atlassian.com/browse/BSP-166]
{quote}
Over the past week, we've seen a drastic reduction in performance on our Bamboo instance. Much of the problem comes from attempting to see test status/failures. 
{quote}

{quote}
Currently bamboo seems to pour tonnes upon tonnes of logs from builds into one log file. It would be exceptionally helpful if there was some kind of option for bamboo to split the logs on say a daily basis
{quote}

From, https://support.atlassian.com/browse/BSP-162

A further improvement would be to seperate build logs from Bamboo system logs.

Originally a support issue, See BSP-157
{quote}
I have followed the instructions at http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO011/5.10.2+Integrating+Bamboo+with+LDAP to enable Bamboo/LDAP integration. This seems to work decently well and pulls users and groups defined in LDAP into Bamboo. This includes mapping some LDAP attributes such as email to corresponding properties on Bamboo users. Is there a way to specify a mapping between LDAP attributes and the Jabber property on Bamboo users?
{quote}

